<br>
Besides that, giants drop Giant Helmets and Toes. Each helmet or toe can be given to Lieutenant Melvin in Skyshrine (Sentry Emil does not exist anymore) for CoV faction. He is a black drake very close to the WL entrance : walk through the gate, turn right, climb stairs and there is Lt Melvin.<br>
<br>
Other advantage of helmets / toes (toes also give you a small amount of cash) is they improve also Yelinak faction (Lord Yelinak is the Chief Dragon of Skyshrine he he ... not the same faction than CoV, like all three majors cities in Velious : Thurgadin = Coldain/Dain  Kael = Kromrif+Kromzek/King Tormax Skyshrine = CoV/Yelinak). Though after the revamp, I saw only Yelinak himself on Yelinak faction, even his closest guards behind the gate were all CoV (ally to me, while Yelinak still threateningly).<br>
<br>
If you are still kos to CoV, just kill enough giants to become dubious, and turn helmets and toes to Lt. melvin when you are on dubious.<br>
<br>
It is preferable to kill bank or Arena giants, as the faction hits are really bigger than the EW/GD giants, where you need to kill hundreds and hundreds for fzction ... so boring .. at least, at Bank (from Lieutenants) or at Arena, you have a chance of armor drops.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps you in your &quot;faction ping-pong&quot; :-)<br>
<br>
